        <h2>Key City Identifiers</h2>
        <ul class="fact-list">
            <li><strong>State:</strong> Rajasthan, India</li>
            <li><strong>Founded:</strong> 1459 AD by Rao Jodha</li>
            <li><strong>Former Capital:</strong> Kingdom of Marwar</li>
            <li><strong>Nicknames:</strong> Blue City, Sun City</li>
            <li><strong>Population (2011 Census):</strong> ~1.03 million</li>
            <li><strong>Primary Economy:</strong> Tourism, Handicrafts, Agriculture</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Major Landmarks</h2>
        <ul class="fact-list">
            <li><strong>Mehrangarh Fort:</strong> The massive 15th-century citadel dominating the city skyline.</li>
            <li><strong>Umaid Bhawan Palace:</strong> One of the world's largest private residences, part hotel and museum.</li>
            <li><strong>Jaswant Thada:</strong> The beautiful white marble cenotaph, known as the 'Taj Mahal of Marwar.'</li>
            <li><strong>Ghanta Ghar (Clock Tower):</strong> The iconic clock tower surrounded by the Sardar Market.</li>
            <li><strong>Toorji Ka Jhalra:</strong> A recently restored historic stepwell.</li>
        </ul>
